 :Wizard Book: /n./ "Structure and Interpretation of Computer Programs" (Hal
Abelson, Jerry Sussman and Julie Sussman; MIT Press, 1984, 1996; ISBN
0-262-01153-0), an excellent computer science text used in introductory
courses at MIT. So called because of the wizard on the jacket. One of the
{bible}s of the LISP/Scheme world. Also, less commonly, known as the {Purple
Book}.